WHEREAS, on March 13, 2020, President Trump declared a national state of emergency in response to the COVID-19 pandemic; and WHEREAS, as of March 16, 2020, there have been two (2) confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Shelby County; and WHEREAS, COVID-19 is a dang is a danger to the health, welfare and economic well-being of the citizens of the City of Memphis (\"City\") and may interrupt municipal services affecting the public's health and safety; and WHEREAS, it is imperative that the City take all necessary measures to contain COVID-19 and prevent its spread throughout the City; and WHEREAS, in the judgement of the undersigned, an emergency currently exists within the City of Memphis as defined in Tennessee Code Annotated $ 38-9-101(2) and $ 58-2-110; and WHEREAS, as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic and its impact on the City, a public health emergency exists in the City pursuant to state and local law; therefore, it is appropriate and necessary for the undersigned to exercise the authority granted by Tennessee Code Annotated $$ 58-2-110, 58-2-104, 38-9-103 and 38-9-104 as well as City of Memphis Code SS 9-8-4 and 2-58-7 and all other applicable law. NOW, THEREFORE, I, JIM STRICKLAND, MAYOR OF THE CITY OF MEMPHIS, by virtue of the power vested in me by Title 58, Chapter 2 and Title 38, Chapter 9 as well as City Code $ 9-8-4 hereby declare a state of emergency exists as it relates to COVID-19 and", "num": "", "path": "library|us/tn|cities/memphis|us/tn/cities/memphis/mayor/declarations/2020-03-12", "title": "City of Memphis Declaration of State of Emergency March 17, 2020.", "url": "/us/tn/cities/memphis/mayor/declarations/2020-03-12"}
